title: Eurovision names Liverpool as host city for its 2023 Song Contest honoring Ukraine
description: The Beatles' hometown of Liverpool, UK will be stepping in to host the festivities at the Eurovision 2023 Song Contest next May, the competition announced Friday.

title: Analysis: Iran's 'women's revolution' could be a Berlin Wall moment
description: The Islamic regime in Iran has ruled for decades with fear and intimidation.

title: Haiti government asks for international military assistance
description: Haiti's government has asked for international military assistance as it grapples with interlocked health, energy and security crises, according to a statement from Jean-Junior Joseph, advisor to Haiti's Prime Minister.

title: US sanctions target Myanmar junta-linked businessman for procuring Russian-made weapons
description: The United States on Thursday imposed sanctions on a Myanmar businessman and two others involved in procuring Russian-made weapons from Belarus for the junta that seized power in the Southeast Asian country early last year, Secretary of State Antony Blinken said.

title: UN rights council rejects debate on China's abuses in Xinjiang in a blow to the West
description: The UN rights council on Thursday voted down a Western-led motion to hold a debate about alleged human rights abuses by China against Uyghurs and other Muslims in Xinjiang in a victory for Beijing as it seeks to avoid further scrutiny.

title: Bolsonaro speeds up payments to the poor as election looms
description: Brazil's government has announced plans to accelerate this month's welfare payments to the needy, as President Jair Bolsonaro prepares to face leftwing rival Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva in a second-round election.
